rayburn.engine.dew.lang

Class DewInterpreter.DewParser.AlgebraicExpressionBranch

  • java.lang.Object
    • rayburn.engine.dew.lang.DewInterpreter.DewParser.AlgebraicExpressionBranch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DewInterpreter.DewParser.BranchElement
    Enclosing class:
    DewInterpreter.DewParser

    public static class DewInterpreter.DewParser.AlgebraicExpressionBranch
extends java.lang.Object
implements DewInterpreter.DewParser.BranchElement
    This class represents a branch that can be attached to the abstract syntax tree, and be evaluated at runtime. This class represents an algebraic expression branch, converted from infix (natural language) to postfix (reverse polish notation) queue for computational evaluation at runtime. Computers can't evaluate infix, so infix is changed to postfix at the parse stage, and queue up for evaluation in an instance of this object.

      • convertNaturalMathToRPN

        public static java.util.LinkedList<DewInterpreter.Token> convertNaturalMathToRPN(java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewLexer.LexicalTokens.LexicalToken> expressionTokens,
                                                                 java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewParser.ParseTokens.Variable> globalVariables,
                                                                 java.util.ArrayList<DewInterpreter.DewParser.ParseTokens.Variable> localVariables,
                                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Short> globalPointers,
                                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Short> localPointers,
                                                                 Logger logger)
                                                                          throws DewInterpreter.DewParseException
        This method parses a natural linear expression and converts it to reverse polish notation (RPN) by using the shunting yard algorithm. Once the natural function has been converted to RPN, it can be evaluated at runtime by the interpreter.
        Parameters:
        expressionTokens - the tokens that describe the expression. Uncleaned for syntax error.
        globalVariables - the ArrayList of variables the expression has access to
        globalPointers - the Map of pointers the expression has access to
        Returns:
        the output queue
        Throws:
        DewInterpreter.DewParseException - if a token is passed that is not a valid expression token, or the syntax rules of the expression are violated, a parse time exception will be thrown
